CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 6, 1941, pg. 11 reads: "The We'Uns Fete Visiting Virginians At Pretty Lawn Party - Members of the popular We'Uns club were invited to the home of Mrs. Wilnette Brooks Jones on Susquehanna street last Saturday afternoon to a lawn party in honor of Mrs. Jones' sisters. Lennie and Juanita Brooks visiting here from Richmond, Virginia.  The cameraman snapped this pretty picture as the guests enjoyed a game of croquette.  Shown in photo are: Mrs. Clyde Paige, Mrs. Carl Deck, Miss Alice Bailey, Mrs. Donald Dammond, Mrs. Alma Berry and the guests of honor.  Mrs. Jones (hostess) is shown at extreme right...Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Thirteen women, most members of the We'Uns Club, including Mrs. Clyde Paige, Mrs. Carl Deck, Alice Bailey, Mrs. Donald Dammond, Alma Berry, Lennie Brooks, Juanita Brooks, and Wilnette Brooks Jones standing on right, in Jones yard on Susquehanna street
